HEADWORD: Double-headed
<hw>Dou"ble-head"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having two
heads; bicipital.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Double-headed rail</b></col> <fld>(Railroad)</fld>, <cd>a
rail whose flanges are duplicates, so that when one is worn the other
may be turned uppermost.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

